track_notes: This is the recommended way to summit Carr Mountain

This is a tough bushwhack.  It shouldnt be...but the ridiculous dense thorny bushes for the first half-mile or so make it so.  It took me well over an hour to go a mile.  Also, I took a bad route up, and ended up in the midst of a heavy rock fall area with loose footing.  I highly recommend following W7JET route, which is closer to my down route and although still thorny, is better.  I ended this hike with tons of scratches, a shredded shirt, torn pants, and a ripped up set of snake gaitors.  If I do it again, I may bring a machete, and push a tarp in front of me through the brush.  On the positive side, I saw a bunch of deer.
